      • follow

        public com.fuse.cms.ModelFollower follow(ModelBase source)
        Create a 'follow connection' between this model and the specified source model, with the default null owner. A 'follow connection' means; this model adopts all of the source model's attributes this model will register listeners to copy changes to the source model's attributes in the future
        Parameters:
        source - The source model to follow
        Returns:
        The created ModelFollower extension instance

      • follow

        public com.fuse.cms.ModelFollower follow(ModelBase source,
                                         Object owner)
        Create a 'follow connection' between this model and the specified source model, and give the connection a specific owner. A 'follow connection' means; this model adopts all of the source model's attributes this model will register listeners to copy changes to the source model's attributes in the future
        Parameters:
        source - The source model to follow
        owner - The owner of the connection (which can be used later to stop the connection; see the stopFollow methods)
        Returns:
        The created ModelFollower extension instance

      • follow

        public com.fuse.cms.ModelFollower follow(ModelBase source,
                                         Object owner,
                                         boolean active)
        Create a 'follow connection' between this model and the specified source model, give the connection a specific owner, and specify if the the connection should be active (also listening to future changes to the source model) or one-time only (just copy the current attributes).
        Parameters:
        source - The source model to follow
        owner - The owner of the connection (which can be used later to stop the connection; see the stopFollow methods)
        active - Flag to specify if the connection should stay active
        Returns:
        The created ModelFollower extension instance

      • stopFollow

        Returns:

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        A list of stopped ModelFollower extension instances
